[SPEAKER_00]: Of course not.

768
01:02:27,140 --> 01:02:31,322
[SPEAKER_00]: So you have to kind of look at it and say, this is a business use, you know, is it an arts and crafts?

769
01:02:31,382 --> 01:02:33,384
[SPEAKER_00]: Is it, you know, how many people is it going to attract?

770
01:02:33,404 --> 01:02:34,364
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, what are the impacts?

771
01:02:34,924 --> 01:02:41,408
[SPEAKER_00]: And so, so I, I think I'm only suggesting this because I just found it to be problematic in the past and to have the

772
01:02:41,628 --> 01:02:59,457
[SPEAKER_00]: I think that the building commissioner, whoever's in this seat should be qualified enough to make a determination, a judgment as to whether or not that use is going to be impactful and, uh, you know, therefore, you know, degrading or, or, you know, some, somehow, you know, more impactful than what a regular type you should be.

773
01:02:59,537 --> 01:03:08,242
[SPEAKER_00]: So, so just something for you to think about, um, under accessory uses, um, this is another one that I, uh, have problem with now and again.

774
01:03:08,262 --> 01:03:09,983
[SPEAKER_00]: Um, so, um,

775
01:03:11,053 --> 01:03:17,637
[SPEAKER_00]: The operation of an accessory use shall not create a visual impact of the premises where located or to the neighborhood.

776
01:03:17,777 --> 01:03:25,862
[SPEAKER_00]: Any accessory activity shall not generate noise, glare, heat, smoke, and I've added this, odor, fumes, or electromagnetic transmission.

777
01:03:26,402 --> 01:03:33,106
[SPEAKER_00]: When an accessory use occurs as part of a business, commercial or industrial use, measures to mitigate all of the above shall be required.

778
01:03:33,746 --> 01:03:39,308
[SPEAKER_00]: Okay, so we, and I'll just finish this off light non nuisance manufacturing shall shall be deemed an accessory use.

779
01:03:39,868 --> 01:03:48,472
[SPEAKER_00]: So, in my opinion, we don't really have mitigation measures for sound, unless it's part of a special permit.

780
01:03:48,672 --> 01:03:48,952
[SPEAKER_00]: Okay.

781
01:03:49,512 --> 01:03:58,862
[SPEAKER_00]: So, I mean, your ability to be able to control those things is fine if you have, you know, an impactful, you know, significant project that's going to be near a residential zone.

782
01:03:59,823 --> 01:04:05,048
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, currently, I have a problem with, you know, residential property in an industrial zone.

783
01:04:05,617 --> 01:04:10,879
[SPEAKER_00]: where I may not have the authority to be able to enforce noise measures, you know what I mean?

784
01:04:10,959 --> 01:04:17,481
[SPEAKER_00]: And so I know that we probably need some help with the noise ordinance.

785
01:04:18,241 --> 01:04:22,542
[SPEAKER_00]: I don't know where in the general ordinances where some measurements are taken from the property line.

786
01:04:22,582 --> 01:04:27,283
[SPEAKER_00]: I haven't had a chance to dig into it enough, but I may make recommendations in the general ordinance as well.

787
01:04:27,964 --> 01:04:32,645
[SPEAKER_00]: But I think that this section needs to be considered, okay?

788
01:04:33,488 --> 01:04:47,678
[SPEAKER_00]: In addition to that, just if I, if I may, on that section, have you, is this just what's currently in the zoning or have you know this is what I suggesting it should be changed to and basically there's no big change to the, to the substance of this is just adding a couple things.

789
01:04:48,619 --> 01:04:49,480
[SPEAKER_00]: Odor is one of them.

790
01:04:50,280 --> 01:05:01,148
[SPEAKER_00]: And I'll say like, again, if you have like recreational marijuana, obviously you can you can make that have all the control but right but things like a bagel factory, you know, I mean people love bagels right they smell great.

791
