804
01:05:28,164 --> 01:05:29,844
[SPEAKER_00]: And then this is another one too.

805
01:05:31,240 --> 01:05:49,079
[SPEAKER_00]: mechanical penthouses now my experience in the, in the city of Waltham mechanical penthouses on laboratories have become enormous, they are 30 feet in height plus, and they can have equipment on top of those when you don't set limits on mechanical penthouses and I think in your current zoning, mechanical penthouse.

806
01:05:49,119 --> 01:05:52,503
[SPEAKER_00]: So basically what they are is these mechanical rooms that are above the roofline.

807
01:05:52,863 --> 01:06:09,850
[SPEAKER_00]: that are exempt from your height in the zoning ordinance and right now there's uh you have like hvac or there's something yes it's usually hvac equipment it could be anything a number of uh things it could be uh elevated penthouse but but what's happening now with laboratories and i expect a big surge of laboratory to come this way

808
01:06:10,911 --> 01:06:29,482
[SPEAKER_00]: What's happening with these is that because there's no limit on the roof and the square footage of the laboratory is so valuable, they're putting most of this mechanical equipment on the roof, not only for more space in the building, but for energy efficiency and the fact that this is where all this hazardous, these fume hoods and so forth are.

809
01:06:30,482 --> 01:06:38,307
[SPEAKER_00]: My concern is that when they get too big, especially with the view of Boston and Boston Harbor and some of the nicer areas here,

810
01:06:38,747 --> 01:06:49,676
[SPEAKER_00]: you could get a conflict where a mechanical room, if there's no limit, and I've seen them have no limit in the last jurisdiction I worked in, they become problematic.

811
01:06:49,856 --> 01:06:57,963
[SPEAKER_00]: And so again, if they're by right and there's no special permit regulation to be able to control those things, they could get pretty much out of sight.

812
01:06:58,043 --> 01:07:03,427
[SPEAKER_00]: So these are parameters that I suggest that I think would work for any laboratory.

813
01:07:03,467 --> 01:07:06,830
[SPEAKER_00]: They wouldn't be restrictive and they would protect the interests of the city

814
01:07:07,430 --> 01:07:13,912
[SPEAKER_00]: and it's a person's right to a view, other than looking at a huge mechanical penthouse.

815
01:07:13,952 --> 01:07:19,594
[SPEAKER_00]: So those are really all the substantive suggestions that I have for now.

816
01:07:20,774 --> 01:07:23,215
[SPEAKER_00]: Again, I would disregard split lots.

817
01:07:23,315 --> 01:07:32,638
[SPEAKER_00]: I think the only suggestion that I'll make is that on the split lot, you have the way it's worded currently,

