822
01:08:04,961 --> 01:08:05,221
[SPEAKER_00]: Sorry.

823
01:08:09,767 --> 01:08:18,495
[SPEAKER_00]: All right, so the way it's worded right now is when a lot is transected by a zoning boundary, blah, blah, blah, the lot may also at the option of the lot owner.

824
01:08:19,863 --> 01:08:23,424
[SPEAKER_00]: be deemed to govern in the smaller part beyond such zoning district.

825
01:08:23,704 --> 01:08:25,285
[SPEAKER_00]: I think this is a really bad idea.

826
01:08:26,185 --> 01:08:39,609
[SPEAKER_00]: This allows a person to be able to expand their industrial use by right 30 feet beyond a zone line that might otherwise protect, it might have bought up to a general residence zone where people are trying to sleep at night.

827
01:08:39,669 --> 01:08:46,331
[SPEAKER_00]: And so my wording is incorrect because it actually increases the impact rather than lessens it.

828
01:08:46,971 --> 01:08:48,672
[SPEAKER_00]: But I think what needs to be,

829
01:08:49,500 --> 01:08:58,704
[SPEAKER_00]: added to this is that if a person wants to expand into their lot, it should be by special permit.

830
01:09:00,545 --> 01:09:02,025
[SPEAKER_00]: So I think that's the best way to do it.

831
01:09:02,065 --> 01:09:03,886
[SPEAKER_00]: Then you're not really changing a lot of substance.

832
01:09:03,906 --> 01:09:06,047
[SPEAKER_00]: You're just directing it.

833
01:09:06,087 --> 01:09:07,668
[SPEAKER_00]: You're not saying that someone can't do it.

834
01:09:07,728 --> 01:09:15,691
[SPEAKER_00]: You're just saying that it's going to require a special permit, or at minimum, site plan review, or SPGA, or community development board.

835
01:09:17,790 --> 01:09:29,135
[SPEAKER_00]: All right, so those are all the changes that I have for now, and I'm gonna work really diligently on this zoning map and get this straightened out, because this is a big priority for the department and for me.

